ZH: 1. 他认定他的朋友是无辜的。
EN: He firmly believes that his friend is innocent.

ZH: 2. 她认定她的选择是正确的。
EN: She is convinced that her decision is right.

ZH: 3. 他认定这个项目会取得成功。
EN: He is confident that this project will be successful.

ZH: 4. 这个证据让我们很容易认定谁是凶手。
EN: This evidence makes it easy for us to identify the perpetrator.

ZH: 5. 她认定她的观点是正确的。
EN: She is certain that her point of view is correct.

ZH: 6. 他认定自己能够完成这项任务。
EN: He believes that he is capable of completing this task.

ZH: 7. 他们认定这个计划将会失败。
EN: They are convinced that this plan will fail.

ZH: 8. 警方已经认定了凶手。
EN: The police have identified the perpetrator.

ZH: 9. 她认定这是她的使命。
EN: She is certain that this is her calling.

ZH: 10. 这些证据让我们很容易认定他是无辜的。
EN: This evidence makes it easy for us to determine that he is innocent.

ZH: 11. 老板认定这个员工是最适合这个职位的。
EN: The boss is convinced that this employee is the most suitable for the position.

ZH: 12. 我们认定这是一个很好的机会，我们必须抓住。
EN: We believe this is a great opportunity that we must seize.

ZH: 13. 父母们认定这所学校是最好的选择。
EN: The parents are certain that this school is the best choice.

ZH: 14. 他认定这是他的使命并努力实现它。
EN: He firmly believes that this is his calling and works hard to fulfill it.

ZH: 15. 这一系列的事件让他们认定这是一场阴谋。
EN: This series of events made them believe that it was a conspiracy.

ZH: 16. 大家都认定他是个诚实可靠的人。
EN: Everyone is convinced that he is an honest and reliable person.

ZH: 17. 民众认定政府应该采取更多的行动。
EN: The public is convinced that the government should take more action.

ZH: 18. 经过调查，警方认定这是一起恶意烧毁的案件。
EN: After investigation, the police determined that it was a case of arson.

ZH: 19. 老师认定这些学生将是未来的领导者。
EN: The teacher believes that these students will be future leaders.

ZH: 20. 我们认定这项计划将带来长期的收益。
EN: We are convinced that this plan will bring long-term benefits.
